14:32:34.635 [INFO] # What I want help with and what stays mine

14:32:34.635 [INFO] I should write this down before convenience starts making decisions on my behalf.

14:32:34.635 [INFO] There are absolutely things I want a personal assistant to help with.
14:32:34.635 [INFO] There are also things that should remain stubbornly human, even if a model could perform a passable imitation of competence around them.

14:32:34.635 [INFO] If I blur those categories, the system will drift toward one of two bad outcomes:

14:32:34.635 [INFO] - it will become overpowered in ways that quietly make life less trustworthy
14:32:34.635 [INFO] - it will become so timid and ceremonial that it stops being useful

14:32:34.635 [INFO] Neither is the point.

14:32:34.635 [INFO] ## What I actively want help with

14:32:34.635 [INFO] ### Continuity

14:32:34.635 [INFO] This is the big one.

14:32:34.635 [WARN] I want help resuming work, reconstructing context, surfacing previous decisions, and preserving enough thread across interruptions that I do not have to repeatedly rebuild my mental state from scraps.

14:32:34.635 [INFO] If I stopped in the middle of something three days ago, I want the assistant to help me restart without theater.

14:32:34.635 [INFO] ### Triage

14:32:34.635 [INFO] I want help separating:

14:32:34.635 [INFO] - urgent from loud
14:32:34.635 [INFO] - meaningful from ambient
14:32:34.635 [INFO] - this week from someday
14:32:34.635 [INFO] - household-critical from merely administratively annoying

14:32:34.635 [INFO] I do not need my priorities invented for me, but I do need the field reduced to something a tired brain can reason about honestly.

14:32:34.635 [INFO] ### Recall

14:32:34.635 [INFO] I want the system to be good at finding the thing I know I already saw:

14:32:34.635 [INFO] - the school note with the one deadline that matters
14:32:34.635 [INFO] - the prior print settings that actually worked
14:32:34.635 [INFO] - the promise I made to a client
14:32:34.635 [INFO] - the shape of a startup thought before I diluted it with seven adjacent thoughts
14:32:34.635 [INFO] - the reminder that a dog walk or lunch break is not optional just because the calendar got louder

14:32:34.635 [INFO] This kind of recall is not glamorous, but it is where a lot of real life is won or lost.

14:32:34.635 [INFO] ### Drafting the boring but necessary text

14:32:34.635 [INFO] I am very happy to delegate first-pass drafting for:

14:32:34.635 [INFO] - follow-up emails
14:32:34.635 [INFO] - meeting recaps
14:32:34.635 [INFO] - reminder phrasing
14:32:34.635 [INFO] - weekly summaries
14:32:34.635 [INFO] - "here is what I think is happening" notes

14:32:34.635 [INFO] As long as the source context is visible and the stakes are clear, this is excellent machine labor. There is no dignity in hand-writing the same moderately careful administrative paragraph for the fiftieth time.

14:32:34.635 [INFO] ### Pattern extraction

14:32:34.635 [INFO] I want help noticing repeated failure modes:

14:32:34.635 [INFO] - the same household friction appearing in new clothes
14:32:34.635 [ERROR] - the same work exception class resurfacing
14:32:34.635 [INFO] - the same client delay mechanism repeating
14:32:34.635 [INFO] - the same kind of overcommitment showing up in my own planning

14:32:34.635 [INFO] This is useful because I am often too close to the week itself to see the pattern until it has already become expensive.

14:32:34.635 [INFO] ### Gentle reminders tied to reality

14:32:34.635 [INFO] I do want reminders.
14:32:34.636 [INFO] I just want better ones.

14:32:34.636 [INFO] Not generic nagging. Not a thousand atomic alerts. I want reminders that understand the difference between:

14:32:34.636 [INFO] - a hard deadline
14:32:34.636 [INFO] - a soft follow-up
14:32:34.636 [INFO] - a brewing risk
14:32:34.636 [INFO] - a household obligation that gets expensive if ignored
14:32:34.636 [INFO] - a personal maintenance item that prevents the whole week from becoming stupid

14:32:34.636 [INFO] That means reminders should be contextual, sparse, and a little opinionated about what matters.

14:32:34.636 [INFO] ## What should stay mine

14:32:34.636 [INFO] ### Commitments

14:32:34.636 [INFO] The assistant should not casually commit me to new dates, promises, scope, purchases, or social obligations.

14:32:34.636 [INFO] It can suggest.
14:32:34.636 [INFO] It can draft.
14:32:34.636 [INFO] It can flag that I am about to overpromise.
14:32:34.636 [INFO] It can prepare the message I might send.

14:32:34.636 [INFO] But the actual act of committing should remain mine unless I have explicitly delegated a very narrow case.

14:32:34.636 [INFO] This matters because commitments are where convenience turns into consequences.

14:32:34.636 [INFO] ### Relationship judgment

14:32:34.636 [INFO] The assistant does not get to decide how I handle emotionally loaded situations.

14:32:34.636 [INFO] It does not get to optimize Petra.
14:32:34.636 [INFO] It does not get to interpret the kids for me.
14:32:34.636 [INFO] It does not get to automate sincerity with friends.
14:32:34.636 [INFO] It does not get to reduce family life to logistics and then claim success because the logistics improved.

14:32:34.636 [INFO] It may help me remember context, summarize facts, or draft something careful.
14:32:34.636 [INFO] But relationship judgment, timing, tone, and emotional accountability stay human.

14:32:34.636 [INFO] ### Value tradeoffs

14:32:34.636 [INFO] There are decisions that are not data problems.

14:32:34.636 [INFO] Should I protect a family evening instead of squeezing in more work.
14:32:34.636 [INFO] Should I choose the boring stable option over the elegant fragile one.
14:32:34.636 [INFO] Should I let a hobby stay a hobby instead of turning it into a side-business possibility.
14:32:34.636 [INFO] Should I accept that some week is already full and stop pretending better planning will save it.

14:32:34.636 [INFO] Those are value decisions. They may use information, but they are not reducible to retrieval.

14:32:34.636 [INFO] I do not want the assistant to smuggle its own optimization criteria into those choices.

14:32:34.636 [INFO] ### Privacy boundaries

14:32:34.636 [INFO] The system should not decide on its own that context is "probably useful elsewhere."

14:32:34.636 [INFO] It should not reuse child-related details in startup notes.
14:32:34.636 [INFO] It should not pull Petra's bureau details into my product thinking.
14:32:34.636 [INFO] It should not remix client specifics into broader pattern language without a visible boundary.
14:32:34.636 [INFO] It should not infer that because I once allowed something, it is now globally fair game.

14:32:34.636 [INFO] Privacy is not just about storage location. It is also about contextual dignity.

14:32:34.636 [INFO] ### The final shape of my attention

14:32:34.636 [INFO] This one is subtle.

14:32:34.636 [INFO] I do want help aiming attention.
14:32:34.636 [INFO] I do not want my attention fully authored by the machine.

14:32:34.636 [INFO] There is a difference between:

14:32:34.636 [INFO] - "these three things look most likely to matter"
14:32:34.636 [INFO] - and "here is the life you should care about today"

14:32:34.636 [INFO] The first is help.
14:32:34.636 [INFO] The second is colonization.

14:32:34.636 [INFO] Even when the assistant is right factually, I want room for human refusal, intuition, guilt, care, curiosity, and the occasional irrational but defensible choice.

14:32:34.636 [INFO] ## The actual division of labor I want

14:32:34.636 [INFO] If I say it plainly, I think the division is something like this:

14:32:34.636 [INFO] The assistant should carry state.
14:32:34.636 [INFO] I should carry judgment.

14:32:34.636 [INFO] The assistant should surface options.
14:32:34.637 [INFO] I should choose when choice matters.

14:32:34.637 [INFO] The assistant should reduce clerical drag.
14:32:34.637 [INFO] I should remain responsible for promises, trust, and meaning.

14:32:34.637 [INFO] The assistant should help me become more consistent.
14:32:34.637 [INFO] It should not make me more machine-like.

14:32:34.637 [INFO] ## Failure modes to watch

14:32:34.637 [WARN] I know how these systems drift, so I want the warning signs written down.

14:32:34.637 [INFO] The assistant is drifting in the wrong direction if:

14:32:34.637 [INFO] - I start shaping life around what is easiest for the system to track
14:32:34.637 [INFO] - I avoid undocumented or private things because the system cannot see them
14:32:34.637 [INFO] - I trust a smooth summary more than a messy reality check
14:32:34.637 [INFO] - I let suggested priorities quietly harden into default law
14:32:34.637 [INFO] - I treat generated tact as equivalent to real care
14:32:34.637 [INFO] - I start believing that anything not captured is somehow less real

14:32:34.637 [INFO] That last one may be the most dangerous.

14:32:34.637 [INFO] Some of the best parts of life are not system-friendly. They are still part of the point.

14:32:34.637 [INFO] ## Working rule

14:32:34.637 [INFO] Use the assistant for memory, continuity, drafting, triage, and pattern detection.

14:32:34.637 [INFO] Do not use it to outsource conscience, intimacy, commitment, or value judgment.

14:32:34.637 [INFO] If that line ever feels blurry, slow down.

